CatDescriptText: Mrs Samuel Mosley, McDonald, Pa, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 1, 1958 with question: "Should parents compel children who are still students in high school or college to work to help support the family?" answer reads: "I don't think so. I think that the children have plenty to do in getting an education."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Samuel Mosley wearing hat, eyeglasses, dark single button coat, and light colored gloves, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
